Lynn.Hitchcock HILLCREST SAPS are appealing to the community to assist them in an inquest case subsequent to a human skeleton discovery in KwaNgcolosi on Monday. Hillcrest SAPS communications officer Constable N. Manqele said a resident Emmanuel Mathe was digging in his yard when he discovered the remains. “A case of inquest was open by Hillcrest police station for further investigation and the bones were taken to Pinetown mortuary,” he said. Anyone who has information regarding this case can contact Detective Constable Makhosi Mvubu on 072 202 5281 or 031 765 9140.  - Supplied.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  